SIMPLE: peal_out
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: peal out
<hw>peal out</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To give off a loud pealing
sound; to peal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To accelerate quickly from a stop in a vehicle,
especially an automobile, so that the tires grind against the pavement
and make a squealing noise while accelerating; -- sometimes performed by
young drivers for showy display.</def> <mark>[slang]</mark> ⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> drop a patch.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pean</ent>⟦br⟧
